Preheat barbecue grill. Combine salsa, ketchup, brown sugar, and mustard in small bowl; remove and reserve 1/2 cup. Place beef steaks on grid over medium, ash-covered coals. Grill, uncovered, 18 to 22 minutes for medium rare to medium doneness, turning occasionally. Brush both sides with remaining sauce during last 5 minutes. Serve with reserved sauce.